# Personal Story Template for LinkedIn

## Hook (Line 1-2)
{The most surprising, emotional, or valuable part of the story. This is the only thing visible before "...see more."}

## Context (2-3 short paragraphs)
{Set the scene briefly. When did this happen? What was the situation?}

{Keep paragraphs to 1-2 sentences. Use line breaks between them.}

{Include a specific detail: a date, a number, a name, a place.}

## The Moment (2-3 short paragraphs)
{What happened? What was the challenge, decision, or turning point?}

{Use concrete details. Avoid abstraction.}

{If there was a specific conversation, quote, or observation, include it.}

## The Lesson (1-2 short paragraphs)
{What did this experience teach you?}

{Frame the lesson so it applies to the reader, not just to you.}

## Close (1-2 lines)
{A question that invites the reader to share their own experience.}

{Or a specific takeaway the reader can apply today.}

---

## Notes
- Total length: 150-250 words
- Every paragraph: 1-3 sentences max
- White space between every paragraph
- At least one specific detail that only you would know
- Do not moralize. Share the experience and let the reader draw conclusions.
